**MiniMax M2.7 prompt length limit (CRITICAL — learned 2026-05-20):**
- Prompts > ~20K characters cause MiniMax M2.7 to return empty response with "⚠️
Empty response from model — retrying (1/3)" and eventual failure
- The FULL_PROMPT in run-daily-blog.sh includes SKILL_CONTENT (22-48KB) + 
TOPIC_CONTEXT + system prompt = easily exceeds 20KB
- **Workaround:** Pass topic context inline in prompt, keep skill content 
minimal, or use shorter skill excerpt
- **Tested pattern that works:** `hermes chat -q "$(cat $PROMPT_FILE)" --model 
MiniMax-M2.7 --provider minimax` with <20KB prompt
- If prompt is large, Hermes chat can return empty — always verify output before
assuming success

**Prerender port 4173 conflict (learned 2026-05-20):**
- `prerender.mjs` binds to port 4173 — if not killed between runs, next 
invocation fails with `EADDRINUSE`
- **Fix:** `fuser -k 4173/tcp` before each build, or kill all node processes 
before prerender step
- This causes build to fail at the prerender step even when esbuild succeeded

**Script variable expansion bug (FIXED 2026-05-20):**
- Lines 161-169 in `run-daily-blog.sh` had `\$` before variables — preventing 
expansion in the prompt
- Fixed: removed backslashes so `${TRACK}`, `${WORKTREE_DIR}`, 
`${TOPIC_CONTEXT}`, `${COMMIT_PREFIX}`, `${BRANCH}` expand correctly
