## tmux Goal Session Pattern

`/goal` dies when the SSH session disconnects. To run persistent goal sessions 
on the VPS:

```bash
# Create persistent tmux session
tmux new-session -d -s goal -x 140 -y 40 'cd /root && exec hermes'

# Attach to goal session
tmux attach -t goal

# Detach without killing: Ctrl+B, D

# Cronjob to auto-start on reboot
@reboot tmux new-session -d -s goal -x 140 -y 40 'cd /root && exec hermes'
```

**tmux session 'goal'** already exists. Gateway must be running as systemd for 
cronjobs to fire — see below.

## Gateway Systemd Prerequisite

**Cronjobs only fire if gateway is running as systemd service.** If gateway 
dies, all scheduled jobs stop.

Check status:
```bash
sudo systemctl status hermes-gateway
```

If not running:
```bash
sudo loginctl enable-linger $(whoami)
sudo hermes gateway install --system --run-as-user root
sudo hermes gateway start --system
```

